tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is impaired, as indicated by elevated creatinine. Mild hyperchloremia is present. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, proteins, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal impairment and consideration of underlying causes, especially given the patient"s advanced age.
